parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Radiator failure can cause engine overheating, leading to damage to the engine and other components, potentially resulting in costly repairs, breakdowns, and even accidents.
An undersized radiator can lead to engine overheating, causing damage to the engine and other components, potentially resulting in costly repairs, breakdowns, and even accidents.
Engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, potentially causing engine failure, breakdowns, and even accidents.

The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the shoulder straps to become loose, fail to lock in position, or not retract, resulting in a loss of protection and increasing the risk of injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: the seat belt does not lock in position
the seat belt does not retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, leading to potential accidents, traffic violations, or difficulty maintaining a safe speed.
symptoms: The speedometer needle does not move
the speedometer displays incorrect or erratic readings
the speedometer is stuck on a specific speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected loss of braking power
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels further than usual
vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
brake warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering king pin seal can cause the king pins to wear out prematurely, leading to loose or wandering steering, which can affect vehicle control and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering feels loose or unstable
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the king pins show signs of excessive wear
the steering system makes unusual noises or vibrations.
